Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), dh-python, fonts-dejavu-core, pybuild-plugin-pyproject, python3-all, python3-aggdraw, python3-numpy, python3-pil, python3-pyproj, python3-pyresample, python3-pyshp, python3-pytest <!nocheck>, python3-setuptools, python3-sphinx <!nodoc>, python3-sphinxcontrib.apidoc <!nodoc>, python3-sphinx-rtd-theme <!nodoc>, python3-versioneer
Description: Draw coastlines, borders and rivers on images (for Python 3) Pycoast is a Python package to add coastlines, borders and rivers to raster images using data from the GSHHG (previously known as GSHHS) and WDBII datasets. . This package is part of the PyTroll toolset.
Package-List: python-pycoast-doc deb doc optional arch=all python3-pycoast deb python optional arch=all
